metadata.name: CA Panico RGB #106
metadata.description:
Another tribute to Stephen Wolfram and his cellular automata, that's a reworking of my previous CA Panico collection.

In this version the RGB basic colors reign supreme, every single color is set by a cellular automata formula, giving life to interesting and particular textures and patterns.

metadata.name: L. T. T. Remainder term #17
metadata.description:
L. T. T. Remainder term

- Using WEBGL1.0
- Textures/Images: None
- 3D Model data: None
- Library: None
- Vertex Shader: 1
- Fragment Shader: 1


Note:
Keyboard m key: Opens the menu. You can save the resolution and the image.
Keyboard f key: fit the screen.
The minimum resolution is 1600px x1600px, but no upper limit is set. The limit is determined by your machine and browser.

GPU is required because of WebGL.

metadata.name: ProtoByte: Scyphozoa.01 #127
metadata.description:
Scyphozoa.01 is the alpha release built with my new ProtoByte.ts library.

ProtoByte is a Verlet Integration-based creative coding framework designed to simulate and render organic, aesthetic structures and behaviors. It combines physics simulation with artistic visualization, offering versatile tools for creating dynamic, whimsically lifelike forms and interactions in 3D.

ProtoByte.ts
Release notes:

As I begin to release #genart projects like Scyphozoa.01, and soon enough the ProtoByte.ts library itself, I thought it would be useful to share my thoughts and hopes for the project. 

I plan to vary minor and major releases in alignment with library development. This drop reflects a minor (though quite significant personally) internal release. Minor releases will generally have more affordable pricing and larger editions.

Project Goals:
1.  Release a fun, distinct and highly useable library, with advanced behavior for creative coding that supports existing core libs such as @threejs, @p5jsArt, @processingOrg, @babylonjs.

2. Develop and nurture a userbase that both create with and contribute to the overall ProtoByte.ts project.

3. Develop supporting pedagogy to continue my 30 year odyssey in #creativecoding. 

4. Continue to contribute to the mission for increased adoption, growth and value of Web3 as a major creative space/art marketplace.

metadata.name: Warped #26
metadata.description:
A free little toy.  Play with it and it might make art!  This is my second project using a shader.  It starts by making a simple drawing, then the shader uses noise to warp the image.  I'm making it free because 1) You really have to work at it to make art (but I think it's a lot of fun to tinker with!), and 2) the capture sometimes has minor variances from the final image - couldn't figure it out.  Made with p5js and uses some Perlin noise code by Inigo Quilez.  

After opening, press "s" to save a large jpg.

metadata.name: As the Wind Blows #86
metadata.description:
As the leaves slowly fall...floating through the winds of winter. A fresh scent wafts through the air, and with it comes youthful memories of hopping on the school bus, waving back at your parents, and staring out the classroom window.

Dreams and the memories of life are never motionless—just as the wind never stops blowing.


Controls:
Double-click to resize the Sketch to your window.
Press S to save a copy of the sketch.

Written in p5js, showcasing the blessings of nature.
Created by Alex and Andrew Mitchell in Autumn 2023
